From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Beau <beau@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] tmux: disable active query escape delay override

Upstream raises escape-time to at least 500ms while terminal capability
queries are active. This protects slow/split terminal replies from being
misparsed as input, but causes a visible Escape delay for tmux popup and
nested tmux workflows.

Respect the configured escape-time instead.
---
 tty-keys.c | 7 ++-----
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tty-keys.c b/tty-keys.c
--- a/tty-keys.c
+++ b/tty-keys.c
@@ -950,11 +950,8 @@
 	if (delay == 0)
 		delay = 1;
 	if ((tty->flags & (TTY_WAITFG|TTY_WAITBG) ||
-	    (tty->flags & TTY_ALL_REQUEST_FLAGS) != TTY_ALL_REQUEST_FLAGS)) {
-		log_debug("%s: increasing delay for active query", c->name);
-		if (delay < 500)
-			delay = 500;
-	}
+	    (tty->flags & TTY_ALL_REQUEST_FLAGS) != TTY_ALL_REQUEST_FLAGS))
+		log_debug("%s: active query; respecting configured escape-time", c->name);
 	tv.tv_sec = delay / 1000;
 	tv.tv_usec = (delay % 1000) * 1000L;
